          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 14876,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "In France, the black market for online gambling is estimated to be worth up to €1.5 billion annually in gross gaming revenue (GGR). In the Netherlands, new spending caps introduced in 2024 have prompted a surge in black market activity. Within months, the black market has surpassed the regulated online gambling market revenue, capturing 51% of the country’s online gambling revenue compared to 49% for licensed operators. The Dutch black market for online gambling is now estimated at €1.25 billion annually based on recently reported revenue data. Similarly, in Sweden, the black market is growing, accounting for 15% of online gambling in 2024, which is equivalent to an estimated €280 million annually.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s20",
          "section_path": [
            "3. Channelling Data"
          ],
