          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 8495,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The EGBA’s proposal to create a common European standard on markers of harm, approved by CEN members, represents a major step for safer gambling in Europe. Markers of harm, changes in online gambling behaviour such as speed, duration, or frequency of play, help identify risky behaviour and support early intervention. The standard establishes a unified list of markers, addressing the current lack of agreement across organisations.",
